Data Scientist		Market Resource Partners		Greater Philadelphia Area		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p></p><p></p><p></p><p>MRP is seeking an experienced Data Scientist to analyze marketing data, with a focus on identifying trends and applying insights to develop successful strategies for optimizing campaign designs and employee performance. The successful candidate will be accountable for analyzing data, building complex SSIS packages, and updating scoring data in our systems using ETL solutions. Extensive previous experience with SSIS and SQL is required. Candidates without demonstrable experience with SSIS will not be considered. </p><p> </p><p>  </p><p> </p><p>Responsibilities: </p><p> </p><ul><li><p>Build, update, and analyze marketing campaign datasets to identify trends, issues, gaps; </p></li><li><p>Help to improve our current lead scoring algorithms by analyzing data and using results to adjust scoring methodologies; </p></li><li><p>Present insights and recommendations to internal and external clients; </p></li><li><p>Analyze disparate client and third party data to answer business questions; </p></li><li><p>Create reports using SSRS, Microsoft Excel and other reporting tools; </p></li><li><p>Build complex SSIS packages; </p></li><li><p>Insert / Update / Delete data using ETL solutions such as Oracle EIM; </p></li><li><p>Learn and translate complex business requirements into SQL code and reports; </p></li><li><p>Write SQL statements and perform database queries and analyses on data from our Siebel CRM.</p></li></ul></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p><span style="text-decoration:underline"><strong>About MRP</strong></span> </p><p>Market Resource Partners (MRP) is a global provider of strategic marketing and demand generation services for the technology industry.  Founded in 2002 and headquartered in Philadelphia, MRP has expanded its reach worldwide with offices around the world.  We specialize in the design and execution of B2B marketing programs, executed both on a local and global basis. MRP enjoys the stability of being part of a larger public company, First Derivatives, PLC (LSE: FDP), a $200 million+ UK-based software and consulting firm. </p><p>  </p><p>www.mrpfd.com</p></div>